.TH "pcix_set_mmrbc" 9 "pcix_set_mmrbc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pcix_set_mmrbc \- set PCI-X maximum memory read byte count
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pcix_set_mmrbc
.BI "(struct pci_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "int mmrbc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
PCI device to query
.IP "mmrbc" 12
maximum memory read count in bytes
valid values are 512, 1024, 2048, 4096
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If possible sets maximum memory read byte count, some bridges have errata
that prevent this.
